data.title: Were there ever multiple kings ruling England simultaneously during the Middle Ages?
data.meta_description:
Answer: Yes, but that was before all the kingdoms were brought together as one country.

Our main kingdoms in Anglo-Saxon England were:

East Anglia

Mercia

Northumbria, including sub-kingdoms Bernicia and Deira

Wessex
